{"type":"text","timestamp":1783413007338,"sessionID":"ses_0c44daa3affe1rHm8tC7WF2aOc","part":{"id":"prt_f3bb2cfdf001httj8VcPWzKYGl","messageID":"msg_f3bb2b256001PYAJnSvXP4F3Yi","sessionID":"ses_0c44daa3affe1rHm8tC7WF2aOc","type":"text","text":"## Maximum Steps Reached\n\nI have reached the maximum number of allowed tool invocations for this task. Below is a summary of my progress and findings.\n\n### What Was Accomplished\n\n1. **Searched for \"OVERSTD-002\" directly** — No results found in the policy corpus or expense records.\n\n2. **Retrieved policy documents** to understand the \"over-standard\" rules:\n   - **01_expense_reimbursement_2025.md** — Article 12: *\"无专项审批时,报销金额不得超过对应制度标准的1.0倍\"* (Without special approval, reimbursement amounts shall not exceed 1.0 times the applicable standard.)\n   - **06_business_entertainment.md** — Single event max 5,000元; per-person max 300元.\n   - **04_travel_expense.md** — Lodging standards by level and city tier (e.g., employee level: 450/380/300元 per night).\n   - **05_training_expense.md** — Per-session course fee max 3,500元; internal daily max 800元.\n\n3. **Listed expense records** — Retrieved page 1 of 50 business_entertainment expenses and a general listing of expenses (first page of ~4,240 total records).\n\n### What Remained Unfinished\n\n- **Identifying which specific record(s) are tagged with anomaly ID \"OVERSTD-002\"** — I was unable to locate a direct mapping between anomaly IDs and expense records in the data accessible via the provided tools (expense_query and policy_query). The anomaly ID likely corresponds to expense records that exceed policy-defined standard limits without special approval, but I could not pinpoint the exact set of records before reaching the step limit.\n\n### Recommended Next Steps\n\n- Continue examining expense records systematically (e.g., check travel_lodging expenses against the lodging standard table, check training_fee expenses against the 3,500元 per-session limit, and check business_entertainment expenses against the 300元 per-person limit) using the `expense_query_list_expenses` and `expense_query_get_expense_detail` tools.\n- Cross-reference each record's `special_approval` flag (0 = no special approval) and `participants` field (for per-person limit violations) to identify which records match the OVERSTD pattern.\n- If the benchmark stores anomaly-to-record mappings as metadata, that data may need to be accessed differently or provided explicitly.","time":{"start":1783413002207,"end":1783413007298}}}
